00:34:32,442 --> 00:34:34,424
We do them on the corners, and we do one overhead.

520
00:34:36,144 --> 00:34:39,085
And it's all listener relative, so it comes out from the listener,

521
00:34:39,126 --> 00:34:40,106
which in our game is the camera,

522
00:34:40,126 --> 00:34:41,527
because I think camera is the best listener.

523
00:34:41,667 --> 00:34:44,149
I don't like to fudge with it and like move it in between

524
00:34:44,409 --> 00:34:46,490
or put it on a spline or put it on a character.

525
00:34:46,530 --> 00:34:48,912
I just like camera because what I see is what I hear.

526
00:34:52,794 --> 00:34:55,856
We then take the data output by the rays

527
00:34:55,896 --> 00:34:56,737
and we do two things with it.

528
00:34:56,777 --> 00:34:58,938
We turn that data into RTBC parameters

529
00:34:59,979 --> 00:35:01,980
that we use to manipulate all the different sends

530
00:35:02,621 --> 00:35:03,821
