00:36:36,682 --> 00:36:39,224
We measure the distance between the ray from the listener

564
00:36:39,304 --> 00:36:40,485
to the object that it's striking.

565
00:36:41,986 --> 00:36:45,128
We use that for attenuating the delays.

566
00:36:45,389 --> 00:36:47,690
So we're interpolating to different delay lines

567
00:36:48,231 --> 00:36:50,092
so that farther away there's a longer delay

568
00:36:50,132 --> 00:36:51,173
before the slap comes back,

569
00:36:51,353 --> 00:36:53,315
and different longer time between the slaps.

570
00:36:55,116 --> 00:36:57,398
And then we use that distance to attenuate it

571
00:36:57,438 --> 00:36:58,298
as though it's getting quieter

572
00:36:58,318 --> 00:36:59,479
because there's no object out there.

573
00:36:59,499 --> 00:37:00,540
It's not actually in 3D.

574
00:37:00,560 --> 00:37:02,302
It's just sending to one that's hard panned.

575
00:37:02,991 --> 00:37:05,232
a bus that's hard panned here, here, in each direction,

576
00:37:05,332 --> 00:37:07,213
matching the orientation of the rays.

